text: Ksenia Igorevna Kurach (; born 1 April 1997) is a Russian sprint canoeist. She participated at the 2018 ICF Canoe Sprint World Championships.C-1 500 m results She won the gold medal at the first ever C-1 500 m women's event. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Russian female canoeists Category:ICF Canoe Sprint World Championships medalists in Canadian Category:European Games competitors for Russia Category:Canoeists at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games medalists in canoeing Category:European Games bronze medalists for Russia
